\cf2 Lord Ganesh Shloka \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf4 Vakratunda Mahakaya\
Suryakoti Samaprabha\
Nirvighnam Kuru Me Deva\
Sarva-Kaaryeshu Sarvada\
\
Meaning:\
O Lord Ganesha, of curved trunk and massive body,\
Whose splendor is equal to a million suns. Please remove all obstacles from my work and in every endeavor.\
This Vandana is both a devotional prayer and a symbolic invocation of focus and clarity. Lord Ganesha represents wisdom, intellect, and the power to overcome challenges. By chanting this, one aligns with mental clarity, removes internal doubts, and prepares the mind and heart for successful action. It emphasizes starting any task with awareness, devotion, and confidence.\
\
