O Goddess Saraswati, who is as fair as the jasmine flower, the moon, and a snow\uc0\u8209 white garland. Who is dressed in pure white and whose hands are adorned with the Veena. Who is seated on a white lotus. Who is ever worshipped by Brahma, Vishnu, and Shiva. May the Goddess protect me and remove all my ignorance.\
