\cf2 Lord Shiva Vandana\cf4  \
\
Shloka (in English script):\
Angikam bhuvanam yasya\
Vaachikam sarva-vaangmayam\
Aaharyam chandra-taaradi\
Tam vande saattvikam Shivam\
\
Meaning:\
I bow to Lord Shiva, whose body is the entire universe,\
whose speech is all forms of expression,\
whose adornments are the moon and the stars,\
and whose very being is pure sattva (divine essence).\
\
This verse sees Shiva as the cosmic dancer, where every movement of the universe is dance. It reminds dancers that their body is a microcosm of the cosmos, and dance is a sacred act connecting the individual to universal consciousness.\
