\
Ishwari Prasad Ji :\
\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf4 Ishwari Prasad, a devotee from Handia (Allahabad), is celebrated as the founder of the Lucknow Gharana of Kathak. Inspired by a dream of Lord Krishna, he devoted his life to reviving Kathak as a form of devotional worship. He trained his three sons\'97Arguji, Kharguji, and Tularamji\'97whose descendants established the Lucknow lineage, blending graceful movements, intricate footwork (chakkars), expressive storytelling (abhinaya), and thumri integration.\
\
The Lucknow Gharana, rooted in Ishwari Prasad\'92s teachings, emphasizes elegance, sophistication, and Bhakti-inspired themes, particularly Krishna-Radha devotion. His family lineage, including notable figures like Prakashji and Thakur Prasad, influenced courtly Kathak under the Nawabs of Lucknow, leaving a lasting legacy on the art form.\
\
