\cf2 Durga Prasad Ji\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf4 Durga Prasad Ji, son of Ishwari Prasad, was a key torchbearer of the Lucknow Gharana of Kathak. Trained rigorously under his father, he mastered the hallmark features of the Lucknow style\'97graceful movements, intricate footwork (chakkars), and expressive storytelling (abhinaya). He performed extensively in the royal courts of Lucknow, where his artistry was highly praised for its elegance and devotional depth. Beyond performing, Durga Prasad Ji was an influential teacher, mentoring the next generation of Kathak dancers and ensuring that the aesthetic and spiritual essence of the Lucknow Gharana was preserved and passed down with fidelity.\
