\fs32 \cf2 Thakur Prasad Ji\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf4 Thakur Prasad Ji, grandson of Ishwari Prasad, emerged as one of the most prominent exponents of the Lucknow Gharana in the 19th century. Renowned for his refined movements, delicate footwork, and emotive abhinaya, he played a major role in popularizing Kathak in the courts of Lucknow, particularly under Nawab Wajid Ali Shah. Thakur Prasad Ji not only performed but also composed and choreographed pieces that integrated Bhakti themes and thumris, enriching the repertoire of the Lucknow style. His dedication to teaching ensured that the lineage remained vibrant, producing a generation of dancers who carried forward the elegance and sophistication of the Lucknow Gharana.\
\
